00:00:07.410 --> 00:00:21.740 align:middle line:90%


00:00:21.740 --> 00:00:24.630 align:middle line:84%
>> Since the dawn
of modern humans,

00:00:24.630 --> 00:00:27.810 align:middle line:84%
every culture in every region
practiced what some would call

00:00:27.810 --> 00:00:30.570 align:middle line:90%
shamanism.

00:00:30.570 --> 00:00:32.530 align:middle line:84%
This mystical
practice is scarcely

00:00:32.530 --> 00:00:35.890 align:middle line:90%
understood but not forgotten.

00:00:35.890 --> 00:00:40.060 align:middle line:84%
In the 1960s, amateur
ethnomycologist, Gordon Wasson,

00:00:40.060 --> 00:00:42.220 align:middle line:84%
wrote his first
book titled, "Soma--

00:00:42.220 --> 00:00:45.550 align:middle line:84%
Divine Mushroom of
Immortality," after noticing

00:00:45.550 --> 00:00:48.400 align:middle line:84%
the indigenous mushroom
culture in Siberia.

00:00:48.400 --> 00:00:51.580 align:middle line:84%
Siberian shamans would collect
the fly agaric or Amanita

00:00:51.580 --> 00:00:54.880 align:middle line:84%
muscaria mushrooms, and
either dried and ate them

00:00:54.880 --> 00:00:57.760 align:middle line:84%
or would feed them to reindeer
and drink the urine to get

00:00:57.760 --> 00:01:00.460 align:middle line:90%
the effects free of nausea.

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:03.620 align:middle line:84%
Because this culture neighbored
ancient Indian culture,

00:01:03.620 --> 00:01:05.860 align:middle line:84%
Wasson surmised that
the Amanita muscaria

00:01:05.860 --> 00:01:09.610 align:middle line:84%
mushroom must be the lost
ingredient of the drink, Soma.

00:01:09.610 --> 00:01:12.070 align:middle line:10%
Soma was the sacred and
psychedelic beverage

00:01:12.070 --> 00:01:13.650 align:middle line:10%
of ancient India.

00:01:13.650 --> 00:01:15.370 align:middle line:10%
But how could this
mushroom have ended up

00:01:15.370 --> 00:01:17.670 align:middle line:10%
in a foreign
religious sacrament?

00:01:17.670 --> 00:01:20.230 align:middle line:84%
This drove Wasson to
dig deeper to discover

00:01:20.230 --> 00:01:23.020 align:middle line:90%
what shamanism truly is.

00:01:23.020 --> 00:01:28.060 align:middle line:10%
>> The term itself came from
the Siberian cultures and was

00:01:28.060 --> 00:01:31.210 align:middle line:10%
brought into English
through Russian and German.

00:01:31.210 --> 00:01:33.010 align:middle line:10%
And people started
to recognize it

00:01:33.010 --> 00:01:35.530 align:middle line:10%
as a phenomenon that was found
in many parts of the world

00:01:35.530 --> 00:01:38.860 align:middle line:10%
and started applying it to
Native American practices,

00:01:38.860 --> 00:01:41.680 align:middle line:10%
into Australian practices,
and things like this.

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:43.720 align:middle line:84%
What really is a
shaman kind of depends

00:01:43.720 --> 00:01:45.430 align:middle line:90%
on the perspective we take.

00:01:45.430 --> 00:01:48.460 align:middle line:10%
>> So the shaman is like
a spiritual bounty hunter.

00:01:48.460 --> 00:01:56.260 align:middle line:10%
He or she deliberately
induces these altered states

00:01:56.260 --> 00:01:59.410 align:middle line:10%
with drugs or other means.

00:01:59.410 --> 00:02:02.190 align:middle line:84%
But then, they don't just
sit there and have the trip.

00:02:02.190 --> 00:02:05.800 align:middle line:84%
They can actually actively
navigate in that world.

00:02:05.800 --> 00:02:10.539 align:middle line:10%
>> The shamans have attained
a sufficient sophistication

00:02:10.539 --> 00:02:16.210 align:middle line:10%
to explicitly understand that
the vessel of our chemical

00:02:16.210 --> 00:02:20.470 align:middle line:10%
transformation is the body.

00:02:20.470 --> 00:02:27.910 align:middle line:10%
And the plants lift the
imprisoning structures

00:02:27.910 --> 00:02:29.140 align:middle line:10%
of the ego.

00:02:29.140 --> 00:02:33.700 align:middle line:84%
And the ego flows
out into the world.

00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:37.180 align:middle line:10%
>> Beyond the confines of
small tribes in Siberia,

00:02:37.180 --> 00:02:40.930 align:middle line:10%
author Gordon Wasson discovered
that larger societies were also

00:02:40.930 --> 00:02:44.230 align:middle line:10%
using psychedelic plants as
a form of societal shamanic

00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:46.860 align:middle line:10%
ritual.

00:02:46.860 --> 00:02:48.990 align:middle line:10%
>> Even in studying
the Hindu culture,

00:02:48.990 --> 00:02:52.540 align:middle line:10%
the Ganges River comes
out of Shiva's top knot.

00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:56.370 align:middle line:10%
In very many depictions, you
see a picture of a cannabis leaf

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:58.170 align:middle line:10%
on top of Shiva's head.

00:02:58.170 --> 00:03:05.580 align:middle line:84%
And also, he's holding a vessel
that contains bhang, B-H-A-N-G,

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:09.750 align:middle line:84%
which is a cannabis-containing
beverage that is flavored with

00:03:09.750 --> 00:03:13.170 align:middle line:84%
cinnamon and cardamom
and other spices.

00:03:13.170 --> 00:03:16.500 align:middle line:84%
And I was also very interested
to learn about the Eleusinian

00:03:16.500 --> 00:03:17.580 align:middle line:90%
Mysteries.

00:03:17.580 --> 00:03:21.210 align:middle line:10%
>> The Eleusinian Mysteries
in ancient Greece clearly had

00:03:21.210 --> 00:03:22.650 align:middle line:10%
a psychedelic sacrament.

00:03:22.650 --> 00:03:24.870 align:middle line:10%
We even know what it was now.

00:03:24.870 --> 00:03:30.360 align:middle line:10%
It a form of ergot
that grows on barley.

00:03:30.360 --> 00:03:32.400 align:middle line:84%
Was used in a beverage
called the kykeon

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:34.690 align:middle line:84%
that initiates of the
Eleusinian Mysteries drank.

00:03:34.690 --> 00:03:38.580 align:middle line:84%
And then, they had extraordinary
and life-changing experiences

00:03:38.580 --> 00:03:39.750 align:middle line:90%
in the dark halls.

00:03:39.750 --> 00:03:42.570 align:middle line:84%
They were addressing,
setting there as well.

00:03:42.570 --> 00:03:44.500 align:middle line:84%
These experiences were
underwent and undergone

00:03:44.500 --> 00:03:46.530 align:middle line:84%
in a place called the
Telesterion, which

00:03:46.530 --> 00:03:49.110 align:middle line:84%
was underground and in
darkness, probably dimly

00:03:49.110 --> 00:03:51.450 align:middle line:84%
lit with little
lamps here and there,

00:03:51.450 --> 00:03:55.080 align:middle line:84%
creating a setting for the
experience to unfold in.

00:03:55.080 --> 00:03:57.450 align:middle line:84%
And the initiates of the
Eleusinian Mysteries,

00:03:57.450 --> 00:04:00.660 align:middle line:84%
who included people like
Plato, people like Socrates,

00:04:00.660 --> 00:04:04.100 align:middle line:84%
people like Cicero, came
out, and afterwards,

00:04:04.100 --> 00:04:05.850 align:middle line:84%
reported that their
lives had been utterly

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:10.920 align:middle line:84%
transformed by the experience
that they had undergone.

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:12.840 align:middle line:84%
They had lost their
fear of death.

00:04:12.840 --> 00:04:14.910 align:middle line:84%
They knew that they
were immortal spirits,

00:04:14.910 --> 00:04:17.640 align:middle line:84%
that they were just temporarily
housed in a human body.

00:04:17.640 --> 00:04:20.940 align:middle line:84%
>> From ancient India to Greece,
psychedelic plants have been

00:04:20.940 --> 00:04:25.290 align:middle line:84%
used for deeply spiritual
quests and large-scale healing.

00:04:25.290 --> 00:04:27.690 align:middle line:84%
But what was the first
well-organized psychedelic

00:04:27.690 --> 00:04:28.890 align:middle line:90%
society?

00:04:28.890 --> 00:04:32.100 align:middle line:10%
Scholars and historians had
all but given up on uncovering

00:04:32.100 --> 00:04:36.960 align:middle line:10%
the mysterious beginnings of the
shamanic society, when in 1976,

00:04:36.960 --> 00:04:40.080 align:middle line:10%
Soviet archaeologist
Viktor Sarianidi unearthed

00:04:40.080 --> 00:04:43.050 align:middle line:10%
the 4,000-year-old temple
complex in present day

00:04:43.050 --> 00:04:44.370 align:middle line:10%
Turkmenistan.

00:04:44.370 --> 00:04:48.090 align:middle line:84%
This complex is nearly a
half a million square meters

00:04:48.090 --> 00:04:51.930 align:middle line:84%
divided into a large northern
and smaller southern region.

00:04:51.930 --> 00:04:57.120 align:middle line:84%
Its walls, made of clay
bricks, span 120 by 150 meters

00:04:57.120 --> 00:05:00.600 align:middle line:84%
and were reinforced by
20 rectangular towers.

00:05:00.600 --> 00:05:05.040 align:middle line:84%
Roughly 6500 to 1700
BC, the northern region

00:05:05.040 --> 00:05:08.400 align:middle line:84%
was burned down, and the whole
complex was abandoned quickly,

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:10.500 align:middle line:84%
leaving the mystery
of its origins

00:05:10.500 --> 00:05:12.870 align:middle line:84%
only with the
artifacts found there.

00:05:12.870 --> 00:05:14.700 align:middle line:84%
Author and researcher
Chris Bennett

00:05:14.700 --> 00:05:17.280 align:middle line:84%
spent years investigating
the spread of cannabis

00:05:17.280 --> 00:05:20.460 align:middle line:84%
in the ancient world and began
piecing the puzzle together

00:05:20.460 --> 00:05:22.620 align:middle line:90%
from this location.

00:05:22.620 --> 00:05:27.090 align:middle line:10%
>> The debate about Soma and
Haoma, the origins of them,

00:05:27.090 --> 00:05:29.280 align:middle line:10%
has changed lately because
of archaeological finds.

00:05:29.280 --> 00:05:31.260 align:middle line:10%
And one of the
really important ones

00:05:31.260 --> 00:05:35.250 align:middle line:10%
is the work of the Russian
archaeologist Viktor Sarianidi.

00:05:35.250 --> 00:05:37.680 align:middle line:84%
He wrote about this
in his book, "Margiana

00:05:37.680 --> 00:05:39.870 align:middle line:90%
and Protozoroastrism."

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:44.610 align:middle line:84%
And Sarianidi he was doing
work in the outer regions

00:05:44.610 --> 00:05:48.130 align:middle line:84%
of Afghanistan, in an area
known as the Bactria-Margiana

00:05:48.130 --> 00:05:50.110 align:middle line:90%
Archaeological Complex.

00:05:50.110 --> 00:05:52.620 align:middle line:84%
And in this region, he found
a number of temple sites,

00:05:52.620 --> 00:05:54.960 align:middle line:84%
and these were big temples,
about the size of a football

00:05:54.960 --> 00:05:55.800 align:middle line:90%
field.

00:05:55.800 --> 00:05:57.900 align:middle line:84%
And half of the
temple sites were

00:05:57.900 --> 00:06:01.350 align:middle line:84%
dedicated to the preparation of
this beverage, which Sarianidi

00:06:01.350 --> 00:06:04.380 align:middle line:84%
has identified as Soma,
Haoma, the sacred beverage

00:06:04.380 --> 00:06:07.200 align:middle line:84%
of the Persians and the
Indians-- ancient Indians.

00:06:07.200 --> 00:06:10.860 align:middle line:84%
>> It is still debated whether
this lost city of Gonur Tepe

00:06:10.860 --> 00:06:15.090 align:middle line:84%
had a supreme ruler or simply
an elite class and high priest.

00:06:15.090 --> 00:06:18.210 align:middle line:84%
In many ways, the priests
of larger civilizations

00:06:18.210 --> 00:06:21.470 align:middle line:84%
mirrored the role of the
predecessor, the shaman.

00:06:21.470 --> 00:06:25.620 align:middle line:84%
>> So, the shaman in the
traditional role is basically

00:06:25.620 --> 00:06:32.370 align:middle line:84%
a liaison for the community to
this realm of the supernatural

00:06:32.370 --> 00:06:35.940 align:middle line:90%
and these supernatural forces.

00:06:35.940 --> 00:06:41.580 align:middle line:84%
So, in that sense, it's kind
of a priest-like function.

00:06:41.580 --> 00:06:44.460 align:middle line:84%
>> At Gonur Tepe, the high
priest was the gatekeeper

00:06:44.460 --> 00:06:47.160 align:middle line:84%
to spiritual and
psychedelic experiences.

00:06:47.160 --> 00:06:49.080 align:middle line:84%
The psychedelic trip
has been equated

00:06:49.080 --> 00:06:51.540 align:middle line:84%
to a mystical
experience, as it allows

00:06:51.540 --> 00:06:54.870 align:middle line:84%
the user to peek behind the
veil of cultural conditioning.

00:06:54.870 --> 00:06:57.840 align:middle line:84%
And the high priest was the
one that bestowed these vision

00:06:57.840 --> 00:06:59.610 align:middle line:90%
quests upon the people.

00:06:59.610 --> 00:07:01.590 align:middle line:10%
Only through his
approval were commoners

00:07:01.590 --> 00:07:03.690 align:middle line:10%
allowed to drink this sacrament.

00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:06.690 align:middle line:10%
Gordon Wasson claimed that
the Amanita muscaria mushroom

00:07:06.690 --> 00:07:10.110 align:middle line:10%
was the psychoactive
ingredient in Soma and Haoma

00:07:10.110 --> 00:07:13.810 align:middle line:10%
because of the mushroom's
common use in nearby areas.

00:07:13.810 --> 00:07:17.550 align:middle line:84%
But this claim is unproven, and
some believe quite implausible,

00:07:17.550 --> 00:07:20.620 align:middle line:84%
due to the kind of experience
these mushrooms elicit.

00:07:20.620 --> 00:07:22.620 align:middle line:84%
Amanita muscaria
mushrooms have been

00:07:22.620 --> 00:07:27.210 align:middle line:84%
known to cause euphoria but
also nausea, sweating, cramping,

00:07:27.210 --> 00:07:28.650 align:middle line:90%
and salivation.

00:07:28.650 --> 00:07:31.380 align:middle line:84%
So, the mystery has
continued through the ages,

00:07:31.380 --> 00:07:34.720 align:middle line:84%
until Victor Sarianidi sent
scraping samples from Gonur

00:07:34.720 --> 00:07:36.900 align:middle line:90%
Tepe out to be analyzed.

00:07:36.900 --> 00:07:40.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Based on archaeological
evidence that's recently come

00:07:40.320 --> 00:07:44.730 align:middle line:84%
up in the last decades, they
found big bowls in the ground

00:07:44.730 --> 00:07:47.820 align:middle line:84%
where the Soma would have
been ground with mortars

00:07:47.820 --> 00:07:51.720 align:middle line:84%
and pestles, and then
also straining devices,

00:07:51.720 --> 00:07:55.600 align:middle line:84%
as well as bowls, with
fossilized remnants in it.

00:07:55.600 --> 00:07:59.070 align:middle line:84%
And so they took some of these
fossilized remnants, which

00:07:59.070 --> 00:08:02.760 align:middle line:84%
was like a fossilized liquid
substance, and had it tested.

00:08:02.760 --> 00:08:06.720 align:middle line:84%
And they found evidence
of cannabis, ephedra,

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:08.010 align:middle line:90%
and in some cases, poppy.

00:08:08.010 --> 00:08:10.830 align:middle line:84%
And all these plants grow in
this region as well, still.

00:08:10.830 --> 00:08:13.290 align:middle line:84%
>> Poppy is the base
ingredient for opium,

00:08:13.290 --> 00:08:16.950 align:middle line:84%
which elicits a sedative and
euphoric effect, while ephedra,

00:08:16.950 --> 00:08:19.080 align:middle line:84%
the basic ingredient
for amphetamines,

00:08:19.080 --> 00:08:21.600 align:middle line:84%
is a stimulant and
appetite suppressant.

00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:25.200 align:middle line:84%
And lastly, cannabis elicits
a slightly psychedelic effect

00:08:25.200 --> 00:08:28.020 align:middle line:84%
with an increase in appetite,
causing this beverage

00:08:28.020 --> 00:08:31.140 align:middle line:84%
to act as a symphony of
mind-altering ingredients

00:08:31.140 --> 00:08:34.530 align:middle line:84%
for these ancient
Indo-European cultures.

00:08:34.530 --> 00:08:37.289 align:middle line:84%
>> And it's interesting it has
his counterpart in the Avestan

00:08:37.289 --> 00:08:40.559 align:middle line:84%
religion over in Persia,
where it's known as Haoma.

00:08:40.559 --> 00:08:44.730 align:middle line:84%
Because of language similarities
and mythological similarities--

00:08:44.730 --> 00:08:47.070 align:middle line:84%
they're both
Indo-European languages--

00:08:47.070 --> 00:08:52.470 align:middle line:84%
this combined use and identity
indicates a much older origin

00:08:52.470 --> 00:08:56.010 align:middle line:84%
from an identical call, so
going considerably far back

00:08:56.010 --> 00:08:56.820 align:middle line:90%
into history.

00:08:56.820 --> 00:08:59.910 align:middle line:84%
We know that they were
involved in trades

00:08:59.910 --> 00:09:01.560 align:middle line:84%
with another
Indo-European culture

00:09:01.560 --> 00:09:05.190 align:middle line:84%
living in central China,
known as the Gushi Culture.

00:09:05.190 --> 00:09:09.960 align:middle line:84%
And we found numbers of
perfectly preserved specimens

00:09:09.960 --> 00:09:13.280 align:middle line:84%
of both cannabis and
ephedra at this site.

00:09:13.280 --> 00:09:17.970 align:middle line:84%
And it's likely that these
Indo-Europeans living in China,

00:09:17.970 --> 00:09:20.370 align:middle line:84%
who were exporting
cannabis, were

00:09:20.370 --> 00:09:24.210 align:middle line:84%
likely the suppliers of the
Bactria-Margiana Archaeological

00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:27.840 align:middle line:84%
Complex's use of it and
delivered by Scythians.

00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:31.180 align:middle line:10%
My view is that the
Chinese term for cannabis,

00:09:31.180 --> 00:09:33.510 align:middle line:10%
which is [NON-ENGLISH],,
traveled with cannabis

00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:37.200 align:middle line:10%
into the Bactria-Margiana
Archaeological Complex with

00:09:37.200 --> 00:09:40.830 align:middle line:10%
this name that became Haoma
and then through dialectical

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:44.610 align:middle line:10%
changes as it reached into
India became Soma in the Vedic

00:09:44.610 --> 00:09:45.870 align:middle line:10%
language.

00:09:45.870 --> 00:09:48.390 align:middle line:84%
>> Along several
ancient trading routes,

00:09:48.390 --> 00:09:51.810 align:middle line:84%
the nomadic horseback Scythians
had burial kurgans that were

00:09:51.810 --> 00:09:54.030 align:middle line:90%
recently unearthed.

00:09:54.030 --> 00:09:55.950 align:middle line:84%
Not only were
golden vessels found

00:09:55.950 --> 00:09:58.470 align:middle line:84%
containing remnants
of cannabis and opium,

00:09:58.470 --> 00:10:02.130 align:middle line:84%
but the frozen tundra preserved
the tattoos on their skin,

00:10:02.130 --> 00:10:04.800 align:middle line:84%
depicting animals
warping and spiraling,

00:10:04.800 --> 00:10:07.440 align:middle line:84%
as if seen in a
psychedelic trance.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:09.630 align:middle line:84%
Ancient Greek
historian Herodotus

00:10:09.630 --> 00:10:12.180 align:middle line:84%
recorded the funerary
rites of the Scythians

00:10:12.180 --> 00:10:15.480 align:middle line:84%
as they built tripod tents
and fumigated cannabis seeds

00:10:15.480 --> 00:10:16.620 align:middle line:90%
inside.

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:18.540 align:middle line:84%
But this wasn't the
only place in history

00:10:18.540 --> 00:10:21.960 align:middle line:84%
we see the use of a tent
with smoke and vapor.

00:10:21.960 --> 00:10:24.250 align:middle line:10%
>> There is a
Polish entomologist

00:10:24.250 --> 00:10:28.440 align:middle line:10%
and anthropologist, Sula Benet,
who suggested that this Hebrew

00:10:28.440 --> 00:10:31.290 align:middle line:10%
term, [? canabasin ?] was a
reference to cannabis and that

00:10:31.290 --> 00:10:36.090 align:middle line:10%
this reference appears for the
first time in the Exodus 30.23,

00:10:36.090 --> 00:10:37.520 align:middle line:10%
where God who--

00:10:37.520 --> 00:10:39.150 align:middle line:10%
appears to Moses
in flames of fire

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:41.010 align:middle line:10%
from within a burning
bush, commands

00:10:41.010 --> 00:10:43.350 align:middle line:10%
Moses to make a
holy anointing oil.

00:10:43.350 --> 00:10:45.510 align:middle line:10%
And every time that Moses
has to speak the Lord,

00:10:45.510 --> 00:10:47.800 align:middle line:10%
he has to go inside
this enclosed tent--

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:50.790 align:middle line:10%
a little area called "the
tent of the meeting."

00:10:50.790 --> 00:10:52.590 align:middle line:84%
And he covers
himself in this oil.

00:10:52.590 --> 00:10:55.800 align:middle line:84%
And he also places some of the
oil on the altar of incense.

00:10:55.800 --> 00:10:58.230 align:middle line:84%
And he speaks to the Lord
and the pillar of smoke

00:10:58.230 --> 00:10:59.987 align:middle line:90%
over the altar of incense.

00:10:59.987 --> 00:11:02.070 align:middle line:84%
None of the other Israelites
in the biblical story

00:11:02.070 --> 00:11:03.153 align:middle line:90%
ever see or hear the Lord.

00:11:03.153 --> 00:11:06.180 align:middle line:84%
